stock-agent — Alembic async migrations

Quick start:
  alembic upgrade head        # apply all migrations
  alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"  # generate new migration
  alembic downgrade -1        # rollback one step
  alembic history             # show migration history
  alembic current             # show current DB revision

Rules:
  - Never edit a migration that has already been applied to production.
  - Always review autogenerated migrations before committing.
  - One logical change per migration file.
  - Import all new ORM models in migrations/env.py so autogenerate can detect them.
